led over a ten-year period. \n\nThe introduction to the collection is by Gerard McDermott.\n\n'The collection captures the colourful and, at times, clashing identities and traditions of different peoples living together, yet separately; their histories and cultures sometimes overlapping, and sometimes conflicting. Some of the photos use allusions, symbolism and subtle references, while others make a virtue of plainness and immediacy. Richard's work maintains either a respectful intimacy or a sympathetic distance: at times, raw and immediate; at other times, detached.' - Gerard McDermott", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 64705780, "asset_id": 12112734, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 11002720, "first_name": "Gerard", "last_name": "McDermott", "domain_name": "cityu-hk", "page_name": "GerMcDer", "display_name": "Gerard McDermott", "profile_url": "https://cityu-hk.academia.edu/GerMcDer?f_ri=2420212", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/11002720/3268019/77363197/s65_gerard.mcdermott.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 113, "name": "Buddhism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Buddhism?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 994, "name": "Journalism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Journalism?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1031, "name": "Southeast Asian Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Southeast_Asian_Studies?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1198, "name": "Peace and Conflict Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Peace_and_Conflict_Studies?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1234, "name": "Thai Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Thai_Studies?f_ri=2420212"}, {"id": 1589, "name": "Photography", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Photography?f_ri=2420212"}, {"id": 2570, "name": "Religion and Thai Culture", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Religion_and_Thai_Culture?f_ri=2420212"