atani", "created_at": "2018-01-10T09:49:55.396-08:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/35634061/Conflict_and_Islamic_radicalism_in_Patani?f_ri=2420212", "dom_id": "work_35634061", "summary": "The insurgent groups in Southernmost Provinces of Thailand are essentially nationalist, although they are waging a jihad and using violence. Unlike transnational jihadist gropus such as ISIS, Al Qaeda and Jemaah Islamiyyah, their use of violence is political in nature, and whenever reasonable negotiatin is offered, they are ready to sit in the negotiation table. The strong influence of the insurgents based on their nationalistic set of ideologies functions as a bulwark against the influence of transnational jihadism. However, it desn't mean that Patani will be free from radicalisation, and for this purpose, fruitful collaboration between the conflicting party through the peace process shall be needed. ", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 55502957, "asset_id": 35634061, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 51084404, "first_name": "Shintaro", "last_name": "Hara", "domain_name": "independent", "page_name": "ShintaroHara1", "display_name": "Shintaro  Hara", "profile_url": "https://independent.academia.edu/ShintaroHara1?f_ri=2420212", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/51084404/16720764/16998198/s65_shintaro.hara.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 3849, "name": "Conflict", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Conflict?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 63483, "name": "Extremism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Extremism?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 80313, "name": "Radicalism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Radicalism?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 140049, "name": "Patani Malays", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Patani_Malays?f_ri=2420212", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1375815, "name": "Patani", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Patan